# editor-blockly (Zelos blocks)

Projects the IR to/from Blockly — the only Blockly-coupled mapping (AD-016).

Before defining/generating blocks, building the toolbox, or wiring serialization, follow
`.cursor/skills/blockly-authoring/SKILL.md`. Look up version-specific Blockly API via the Context7
MCP (Blockly is pinned at M0) — never from memory; **use JSON serialization, never the XML API**.

## Rules

- **Variants over hidden modes** (AD-015): one palette block per parameter shape; never a hidden mode
  dropdown. Dropdowns only for small constant choices (operator/function names, enums; FR-058).
- Generic blocks are generated at runtime from metadata; specialized blocks are TS overrides selected
  by `rule_name`/`variant_id`. A registry resolves specialized over generic, and **both must emit
  identical JSON per variant** (AD-014).
- Block/palette labels show both the friendly title and the rule name, e.g. `Get attribute (attr)` (§12.5).
- The toolbox uses the canonical categories (§12.4); progressive disclosure via the advanced flag plus
  palette search (§12.6).
- Required inputs are visually marked; a variant missing required inputs is visually invalid and must
  not export as valid (FR-056/057).
- Output types (§13.1) are advisory UX hints — they must not override engine validation (AD-013).
- Default renderer is Zelos (AD-017); render in light DOM with scoped CSS (AD-018).
